    slug: "islam-a-total-beginners-guide-1",
    description: `Islam A Total Beginners Guide (1) is the first volume in a comprehensive English-language series designed to introduce Islam to people who have little or no prior knowledge of the religion, including new converts to Islam, non-Muslims seeking to understand what Islam teaches, young adults, and anyone who wants a clear, structured, and accurate overview of the foundational principles and practices of the Islamic faith. The first volume focuses on the most essential aspects of Islam that a beginner needs to understand, presenting them in a straightforward and accessible manner without assuming any prior familiarity with Islamic terminology, history, or theology. The book avoids both the apologetic excess and the academic density that characterize many introductory Islamic texts, instead offering a balanced, informative, and engaging presentation that respects the reader's intelligence while remaining easy to follow.

The book opens with an introduction to the very concept of religion from an Islamic perspective, explaining what Islam teaches about the purpose of human existence, the relationship between the Creator and creation, and the role of prophets and revealed books in guiding humanity. It then introduces the fundamental Islamic creed (aqeedah), explaining the six pillars of iman (faith) in Islam: belief in Allah, belief in His angels, belief in His revealed books, belief in His messengers, belief in the Day of Judgment, and belief in divine predestination (qadar). Each article of faith is explained with clarity and depth, using language that a complete beginner can understand while conveying the substance and significance of each belief. The section on belief in Allah covers the Islamic concept of God's oneness (tawheed), His attributes, and the difference between the Islamic understanding of God and common misconceptions.

The second major section of the book introduces the five pillars of Islam, which are the practical acts of worship that form the foundation of a Muslim's religious life: the declaration of faith (shahadah), the five daily prayers (salah), obligatory charity (zakah), fasting during Ramadan (sawm), and the pilgrimage to Makkah (hajj). For each pillar, the book provides a clear explanation of what it entails, why it is important, and how it is performed, with enough detail to give the reader a thorough understanding without overwhelming them with the complexities that are covered in more advanced texts. The book also includes a section on the life of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him), presenting a concise biography that covers the major events of his life and his role as the final messenger of Allah. The English prose is clear, engaging, and free from jargon, making this first volume an excellent starting point for anyone beginning their exploration of Islam.`,
    metaDescription: "Islam A Total Beginners Guide 1 introduces Islamic creed, five pillars, and the Prophet's life in clear English. Perfect for new Muslims and seekers."
