    slug: "islam-a-total-beginners-guide-3-vols",
    description: `Islam a Total Beginners Guide (3 Vols) is the complete three-volume set of the comprehensive English-language introductory series on Islam, designed as a single package that takes a reader with no prior knowledge of Islam through a progressively deeper understanding of the religion's beliefs, practices, history, and spiritual dimensions. This three-volume set is ideal for new Muslims who want a thorough foundation in their new faith, for Islamic schools and educational institutions that need a structured curriculum for teaching Islam to beginners, for dawah organizations and individuals who want a reliable resource to share with people interested in learning about Islam, and for any English-speaking reader who wants a comprehensive yet accessible reference work on the Islamic faith presented in a single coordinated set.

Volume One of the set covers the absolute fundamentals of Islam, including the Islamic creed (aqeedah) with detailed explanations of the six articles of faith, the five pillars of Islam with practical guidance on performing each one, an introduction to the life and mission of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him), and basic Islamic etiquette and morals that every Muslim should know. This volume establishes the conceptual foundation upon which the subsequent volumes build. Volume Two expands the reader's knowledge by covering the broader framework of Islamic teachings, including detailed guidance on personal worship and spiritual development, the Islamic approach to family life and social relations, the principles of Islamic ethics and character development, and an introduction to Islamic history from the time of the Prophet through the major historical periods and civilizations of the Muslim world. Volume Three addresses more advanced and specialized topics, including Islamic law and jurisprudence (shariah and fiqh) at an introductory level, the Islamic perspective on contemporary issues, the spiritual dimensions of Islam including Sufism and the purification of the soul, comparative religion from an Islamic standpoint, and guidance for continued learning and personal development as a Muslim.

Throughout all three volumes, the series maintains a consistent pedagogical approach that combines clear explanations with practical guidance, making abstract concepts tangible and actionable. Each chapter includes review questions, key terms and definitions, and suggestions for further reading, making the set suitable for both self-study and classroom instruction. The three volumes together provide a comprehensive education in Islam that is equivalent to what a student might receive in an introductory Islamic studies course at a university or Islamic seminary, but presented in language and a format that is accessible to the general reader. The English prose is engaging and supportive, encouraging the reader to continue their learning journey with confidence and enthusiasm. This complete set is one of the most thorough and well-organized introductory resources on Islam available in the English language.`,
